{"ID":"20250513160407-6tsh8he","Spec":"1","Type":"NodeDocument","Properties":{"id":"20250513160407-6tsh8he","title":"2022-ICMSE-An Empirical Study on Performance Bugs in Deep Learning Frameworks","type":"doc","updated":"20250513160902"},"Children":[{"ID":"20250513160632-6ygb7yb","Type":"NodeHeading","HeadingLevel":1,"Properties":{"id":"20250513160632-6ygb7yb","updated":"20250513160720"},"Children":[{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"摘要"}]},{"ID":"20250513160711-cbmx8ih","Type":"NodeParagraph","Properties":{"id":"20250513160711-cbmx8ih","updated":"20250513160711"},"Children":[{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"本研究针对当前主流的深度学习框架——TensorFlow 和 PyTorch，系统地挖掘了两者 GitHub 仓库中的性能相关和非性能相关 bug，通过量化分析和手工归类，回答了三大研究问题：性能 bug 随时间的演化趋势、性能 bug 与非性能 bug 在修复难度和社区参与度上的差异，以及性能 bug 的根本原因分类。研究发现，性能 bug 的新增速度超过修复速度，性能 bug 在所有 bug 中所占比例逐年上升；性能 bug 的修复周期（中位数 20 天 vs. 10 天）、修复代码量（中位数 38 LOC vs. 28 LOC）及讨论热度均显著高于非性能 bug；基于141 个已修复的性能 bug，作者构建了涵盖 12 大类、19 个子类的性能 bug 归因分类；最后，论文给出了面向研究者和框架开发者的可操作性建议，旨在推动更有效的性能测试和框架优化。"}]},{"ID":"20250513160711-gmw7d0i","Type":"NodeHeading","HeadingLevel":1,"Properties":{"id":"20250513160711-gmw7d0i","updated":"20250513160726"},"Children":[{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"背景与动机"}]},{"ID":"20250513160711-l1yomik","Type":"NodeParagraph","Properties":{"id":"20250513160711-l1yomik","updated":"20250513160711"},"Children":[{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"深度学习（DL）因大规模数据和硬件资源可用性而迅速普及，TensorFlow 与 PyTorch 等开源框架的质量直接影响下游应用的性能与可靠性"},{"Type":"NodeTextMark","TextMarkType":"a","TextMarkAHref":"https://petertsehsun.github.io/papers/performance_issues_study.pdf","TextMarkTextContent":"petertsehsun.github.io"},{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"。"}]},{"ID":"20250513160711-7jksowp","Type":"NodeParagraph","Properties":{"id":"20250513160711-7jksowp","updated":"20250513160711"},"Children":[{"Type":"NodeText","Data":"DL 框架的性能优化面临独有挑战，如多硬件集成、重复迭代计算和细粒度内存管理等，这些特性使得性能 bug 更难检测与修复"},{"Type":"NodeTextMark","TextMarkType":"a","TextMarkAHref":"https://petertsehsun.github.io/papers/performance_issues_study.pdf","TextMarkTextCont